data.name: Balloon Stand
data.oracle_text:
Visit — Choose one.
• Create a 1/1 red Balloon creature token with flying.
• Sacrifice a Balloon. If you do, target creature gains flying until end of turn.
data.flavor_text: Buy enough balloons and it turns into a ride.

data.name: Bounce Chamber
data.oracle_text: Visit — Return a creature you don't control with the lowest toughness among creatures you don't control to its owner's hand. (If multiple creatures are tied, choose any one of them.)
data.flavor_text: The Astrotorium bouncing record is three days, though setting it wasn't strictly intentional.

data.name: Bumper Cars
data.oracle_text: Visit — Target creature must be blocked this turn if able.
data.flavor_text:
"These bumping cars remind me of the time your amusement park smashed into my planet."
—Ambassador Blorpityblorpboop

data.name: Centrifuge
data.oracle_text: Visit — Each player draws a card from the library of the player to their right. You create three Treasure tokens.
data.flavor_text: Originally, the rotors were used exclusively as particle accelerators for engine fuel, and they probably still should be.

data.name: Clown Extruder
data.oracle_text: Visit — Create a 1/1 white Clown Robot artifact creature token.
data.flavor_text: The sound it makes is indescribable and unsettling, but it does make a great clown.

data.name: Concession Stand
data.oracle_text: Visit — Create a Food token. (It's an artifact with "{2}, {T}, Sacrifice this artifact: You gain 3 life.")
data.flavor_text: Eating here is always a concession.

data.name: Costume Shop
data.oracle_text: Visit — You may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own.
data.flavor_text: Outfits you'll love at prices you'll tolerate.

data.name: Cover the Spot
data.oracle_text:
Visit — Drop three cards you own from outside the game one at a time onto the playing area from a height of at least one foot (about 0.3 meters). If those cards completely cover Cover the Spot, claim the prize!
Prize — You get {TK}{TK}{TK}{TK}, then you may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own. Sacrifice Cover the Spot, then open an Attraction.

data.name: Dart Throw
data.oracle_text:
Visit — Throw a card you own from outside the game onto the playing area from a distance of three feet (about one meter). If that card touches Dart Throw, claim the prize!
Prize — Create two 2/2 pink Teddy Bear creature tokens. Sacrifice Dart Throw, then open an Attraction.

data.name: Drop Tower
data.oracle_text: Visit — Target creature gains flying until end of turn, or until any player rolls a 1, whichever comes first.
data.flavor_text: "I can see the next star system from here!"

data.name: Ferris Wheel
data.oracle_text: Visit — Choose target creature that hasn't been phased out with Ferris Wheel. That creature phases out until you roll a 3 or less while rolling to visit your Attractions.
data.flavor_text: After a certain point, it becomes more of a prison than a ride.

data.name: Foam Weapons Kiosk
data.oracle_text: Visit — Put a +1/+1 counter on target creature you control. That creature gains vigilance until end of turn.
data.flavor_text: Nothing is safe in the hands of an eight-year-old.

data.name: Fortune Teller
data.oracle_text: Visit — Scry 1.
data.flavor_text: TODAY'S FORTUNE: YOU WILL REGRET SPENDING YOUR MONEY ON THIS FORTUNE.

data.name: Gallery of Legends
data.oracle_text: Visit — Exile cards from the top of your library until you exile a nonland card, then choose a legendary creature card name with the same mana value as that card. Create a token that's a copy of the card with the chosen name. That token gains haste. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step.

data.name: Gift Shop
data.oracle_text:
Visit — Choose one that hasn't been chosen.
• Create a 1/1 red Balloon creature token with flying.
• Create a 2/2 pink Teddy Bear creature token.
• Create two Food tokens.
• You get {TK}{TK}{TK}.
• You may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own.

data.name: Guess Your Fate
data.oracle_text:
Visit — Look at the bottom of your library, then give a person outside the game a one-word clue not on that card. They guess a word. If their guess appears in that card's name, claim the prize!
Prize — Reveal the card, put it into your hand, then sacrifice Guess Your Fate and open an Attraction.

data.name: Hall of Mirrors
data.oracle_text: Visit — Choose target creature you control. Each other creature you control becomes a copy of that creature until end of turn, except it isn't legendary.
data.flavor_text: For a smaller fee, you can pop in quickly to try on a pair of jeans.

data.name: Haunted House
data.oracle_text: Visit — Return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield. It gains haste. Exile it at the beginning of your next end step.
data.flavor_text: To build Sorin's Haunted Mansion, every detail of Markov Manor was painstakingly recreated, from the floating laser ghosts to the robot space gargoyles.

data.name: Information Booth
data.oracle_text: Visit — Draw a card.
data.flavor_text: "Sir, this may be the information booth, but I cannot answer ontological questions. It would be arrogant to assume I could describe the true nature of reality. Also there's a line."

data.name: Kiddie Coaster
data.oracle_text: Visit — Creatures you control get +1/+0 until end of turn.
data.flavor_text: The only ride that's never failed a safety inspection.

data.name: Log Flume
data.oracle_text: Visit — Choose up to four creatures you control. Those creatures jump in a log until end of turn. (Creatures in a log together can't be blocked unless they're all blocked. If a spell or ability you control targets one of them, it targets all of them.)
data.flavor_text: "Keep your hands and feet inside me at all times and enjoy the glubbbbrbb! Glbbglubb! Glb!"

data.name: Memory Test
data.oracle_text:
When Memory Test enters the battlefield, target opponent exiles cards from the bottom of their library until they exile five nonland cards, then turn those nonland cards face down.
Visit — Name the exiled face-down cards, then look at them. If you named them correctly, turn them face up, then claim the prize!
Prize — Create three 1/1 red Balloon creature tokens with flying, then sacrifice Memory Test and open an Attraction.

data.name: Merry-Go-Round
data.oracle_text: Visit — Creatures you control with power 2 or less gain horsemanship until end of turn. (They can't be blocked except by creatures with horsemanship.)
data.flavor_text: Ensconced in a slow time bubble that makes a five-minute ride take nine hours, the carousel is a very popular childcare option.

data.name: Pick-a-Beeble
data.oracle_text:
Visit — Roll a six-sided die. Put a number of luck counters on Pick-a-Beeble equal to the result and create a Treasure token. Then if there are six or more luck counters on Pick-a-Beeble, claim the prize!
Prize — Create two Treasure tokens, then sacrifice Pick-a-Beeble and open an Attraction.

data.name: Push Your Luck
data.oracle_text:
Visit — Reveal cards from the top of your library until you decide to stop. If the total mana value of the cards revealed this way is 7 or less, create a 2/2 pink Teddy Bear creature token. If the total is exactly 7, claim the prize! Shuffle the revealed cards into your library.
Prize — Put five +1/+1 counters on a Teddy Bear you control. It gains haste. Sacrifice Push Your Luck and open an attraction.

data.name: Roller Coaster
data.oracle_text: Visit — Creatures you control get +2/+0 until end of turn.
data.flavor_text: Every rider leaves The Fluctuator happy—most because they're thrilled to still be alive.

data.name: Scavenger Hunt
data.oracle_text:
Visit — Choose "a creature wearing a hat," "a book or scroll", or "teeth" at random. You have ten seconds to search your library and reveal a card with the chosen item in its art. If you do, claim the prize! Then shuffle.
Prize — You get {TK}{TK}, then you may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own. Sacrifice Scavenger Hunt and open an Attraction.

data.name: Scavenger Hunt
data.oracle_text:
Visit — Choose "a four-legged creature," "a liquid other than water", or "a door" at random. You have ten seconds to search your library and reveal a card with the chosen item in its art. If you do, claim the prize! Then shuffle.
Prize — You get {TK}{TK}, then you may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own. Sacrifice Scavenger Hunt and open an Attraction.

data.name: Scavenger Hunt
data.oracle_text:
Visit — Choose "a humanoid animal or alien," "food," or "horns and tusks" at random. You have ten seconds to search your library and reveal a card with the chosen item in its art. If you do, claim the prize! Then shuffle.
Prize — You get {TK}{TK}, then you may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own. Sacrifice Scavenger Hunt and open an Attraction.

data.name: Scavenger Hunt
data.oracle_text:
Visit — Choose "an elf or goblin," "a tail", or "a flying creature or flying vehicle" at random. You have ten seconds to search your library and reveal a card with the chosen item in its art. If you do, claim the prize! Then shuffle.
Prize — You get {TK}{TK}, then you may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own. Sacrifice Scavenger Hunt and open an Attraction.

data.name: Scavenger Hunt
data.oracle_text:
Visit — Choose "a vampire or zombie," "fire, lightning, or an explosion", or "a metallic creature" at random. You have ten seconds to search your library and reveal a card with the chosen item in its art. If you do, claim the prize! Then shuffle.
Prize — You get {TK}{TK}, then you may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own. Sacrifice Scavenger Hunt and open an Attraction.

data.name: Scavenger Hunt
data.oracle_text:
Visit — Choose "a weapon," "five or more creatures", or "words or numbers" at random. You have ten seconds to search your library and reveal a card with the chosen item in its art. If you do, claim the prize! Then shuffle.
Prize — You get {TK}{TK}, then you may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own. Sacrifice Scavenger Hunt and open an Attraction.

data.name: Spinny Ride
data.oracle_text: Visit — Tap target creature an opponent controls.
data.flavor_text:
"The ship spinning out of control was spot-on, but no one shouting, 'Nebula! You fell asleep again!' or openly weeping? Too unrealistic."
—Captain Rex Nebula

data.name: Squirrel Stack
data.oracle_text:
Visit — You have five seconds to stack dice on top of one another. If you stack at least five dice, claim the prize!
Prize — Create a 1/1 green Squirrel creature token for each die you stack above the fourth, then sacrifice Squirrel Stack and open an Attraction.

data.name: Storybook Ride
data.oracle_text: Visit — Exile the top X cards of your library, where X is the number of Attractions you've visited this turn (including this one). You may play those cards this turn. At the beginning of the next end step, if any of those cards remain exiled, put them on the bottom of your library in any order.
data.flavor_text: The ride is whimsical and fun, except when it's broken.

data.name: Swinging Ship
data.oracle_text: Visit — After the first combat phase this turn, there's an additional combat phase. At the beginning of that combat, untap all creatures that attacked this turn.
data.flavor_text:
"I feel just like Kari Zev! Ragavan, set a course for Lathnu!"
—Vorthos, Steward of Myth

data.name: The Superlatorium
data.oracle_text:
Visit — An opponent chooses "the cleanest," "the hungriest," or "the strangest." You choose a creature, then ask a person outside the game to choose the creature that best fits the chosen criteria. If they chose the same creature you chose, claim the prize!
Prize — Create two 1/1 red Balloon creature tokens with flying, then sacrifice The Superlatorium and open an Attraction.

data.name: The Superlatorium
data.oracle_text:
Visit — An opponent chooses "the cutest," "the loudest," or "the strongest." You choose a creature, then ask a person outside the game to choose the creature that best fits the chosen criteria. If they chose the same creature you chose, claim the prize!
Prize — Create two 1/1 red Balloon creature tokens with flying, then sacrifice The Superlatorium and open an Attraction.

data.name: The Superlatorium
data.oracle_text:
Visit — An opponent chooses "the fastest," "the scariest," or "the weakest." You choose a creature, then ask a person outside the game to choose the creature that best fits the chosen criteria. If they chose the same creature you chose, claim the prize!
Prize — Create two 1/1 red Balloon creature tokens with flying, then sacrifice The Superlatorium and open an Attraction.

data.oracle_text:

Prize — Create two 1/1 red Balloon creature tokens with flying, then sacrifice The Superlatorium and open an Attraction.

data.oracle_text:

Prize — Create two 1/1 red Balloon creature tokens with flying, then sacrifice The Superlatorium and open an Attraction.

data.name: The Superlatorium
data.oracle_text:
Visit — An opponent chooses "the quietest," "the slowest," or "the ugliest." You choose a creature, then ask a person outside the game to choose the creature that best fits the chosen criteria. If they chose the same creature you chose, claim the prize!
Prize — Create two 1/1 red Balloon creature tokens with flying, then sacrifice The Superlatorium and open an Attraction.

data.name: Trash Bin
data.oracle_text: Visit — Mill two cards, then return a card at random from your graveyard to your hand. (To mill a card, a player puts the top card of their library into their graveyard.)
data.flavor_text: "I had to wrestle a squirrel for it, but I won!"

data.name: Trivia Contest
data.oracle_text:
Visit — An opponent chooses black card, artifact card, or expansion, then mills a card. You have ten seconds to name something from the chosen category that starts with the same letter as the milled card. If you do, claim the prize!
Prize — You get {TK}{TK}{TK}, then you may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own. Sacrifice Trivia Contest and open an Attraction.

data.name: Trivia Contest
data.oracle_text:
Visit — An opponent chooses blue card, enchantment card, or creature type, then mills a card. You have ten seconds to name something from the chosen category that starts with the same letter as the milled card. If you do, claim the prize!
Prize — You get {TK}{TK}{TK}, then you may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own. Sacrifice Trivia Contest and open an Attraction.

data.name: Trivia Contest
data.oracle_text:
Visit — An opponent chooses green card, instant card, or named mechanic, then mills a card. You have ten seconds to name something from the chosen category that starts with the same letter as the milled card. If you do, claim the prize!
Prize — You get {TK}{TK}{TK}, then you may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own. Sacrifice Trivia Contest and open an Attraction.

data.name: Trivia Contest
data.oracle_text:
Visit — An opponent chooses white card, land card, or planeswalker card, then mills a card. You have ten seconds to name something from the chosen category that starts with the same letter as the milled card. If you do, claim the prize!
Prize — You get {TK}{TK}{TK}, then you may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own. Sacrifice Trivia Contest and open an Attraction.

data.name: Trivia Contest
data.oracle_text:
Visit — An opponent choses colorless card, creature card, or plane, then mills a card. You have ten seconds to name something from the chosen category that starts with the same letter as the milled card. If you do, claim the prize!
Prize — You get {TK}{TK}{TK}, then you may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own. Sacrifice Trivia Contest and open an Attraction.

data.name: Trivia Contest
data.oracle_text:
Visit — An opponent choses red card, sorcery card, or legendary card, then mills a card. You have ten seconds to name something from the chosen category that starts with the same letter as the milled card. If you do, claim the prize!
Prize — You get {TK}{TK}{TK}, then you may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own. Sacrifice Trivia Contest and open an Attraction.

data.name: Tunnel of Love
data.oracle_text: Visit — Choose an opponent. They choose a creature you control, then you choose a creature they control. You may exile the chosen creatures. If you do, return them to the battlefield under their owners' control at the beginning of the next end step. Otherwise, the chosen creatures fight each other.
